    <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545"> 
      <head altrender="biography" id="a2">BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE </head> 
      <p>National Sustainable Agricultural Coalition (NSAC), based in
        Washington, D. C., was created out of two successful grassroots organizations,
        the Sustainable Agriculture Coalition (SAC) and the National Campaign for
        Sustainable Agriculture (NCSA). The National Sustainable Agriculture Coalition
        (NSAC) is a national alliance of farm, rural development, and conservation
        groups that organized in 1988 to affect federal agriculture policy. NSAC's
        vision of agriculture is one where a safe, nutritious, ample, and affordable
        food supply is produced by a legion of family farmers who make a decent living
        pursuing their trade, while protecting the environment, and contributing to the
        strength and stability of their communities.</p> 
    </bioghist> 
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520"> 
      <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head> 
      <p>The collection contains correspondence, memoranda, meeting minutes,
        reports, and logo templates designed by Bonnie Acker.</p> 
    </scopecontent> 
